 (segmentation, struts) and for some aberrations evolving over\nthe life of the instrument (residual phase aberrations, artifacts in the\naperture, misalignments in the coronagraph design). This technique can now\nobtain the earth-like planet detection threshold of 10^(-10) contrast on any\ngiven aperture over at least a 10% spectral bandwidth, with several coronagraph\ndesigns.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Sep 2017 18:49:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-20"}
